<br>
Ok, well they are underwater..NP, I have a fishbone earring..I can pull 2 with no problem..I need 4 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have tried to levitate to expedite my run to land ..I have tried levitating aggroing them with temp flux staff..but getting 4 together seems to only happen if I aggro 2, go up to surface..run with Jboots to other corner, dive all the way down to aggro other 2, go up to surface  with the other 2 gobs wacking me, and flee to shore..THEN begin kite...whew..this is the easy exp ?<br>
<br>
What am I missing ?  Sometimes while doing this, Ill end up with 6 on shore<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    What is the tactic for getting the needed 4 without overpulling ?  I end up with 2 or 5+ usually..is there a key corner ? or an area where you can get the 4 ?  They swim very fast BTW, and even with 200 swim skill, you need levitate to survive it seems..any advice would be appreciated.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/01 12:48:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding Bloodgills..</span><hr size=1> See the pain in the ass?  I loved quading in omen at 29-34 but it seems to have gotten harder.  And I still get that last one 4th mob who wanders when i turn to face them.  When I turn to run it startys after me again but it is out of sych with the rest and never gets snared and fubars the whole thing.  I level steady but not as fast soloing blues single style.  I'm 42 and in EW killing most blues near zoneline and liking it.  When I hit 44 I may try bloodgills single.  May want to find an easier mob to pull though and ina less crowded zone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uskystormthunderbolt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SkystormThunderbolt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 2:04:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding Bloodgills..</span><hr size=1> I tried Bloodgills last night on my server, each spawn spot was camped, I couldn't beleive it...<br>
<br>
Is this the way with most servers? Because there seems to be less people camping Spectres than Bloodgills on mine...<br>
<br>
I sure hope I was unlucky - otherwise I guess I will go back to partnering with my Enc friend at Dreadlands.<br>
<br>
Skystorm Thunderbolt<br>
44th Wizard - Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uknolanncaelestis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knolann Caelestis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/11/01 4:39:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding Bloodgills..</span><hr size=1> I quadded these for awhile no problem. Info:<br>
<br>
At certain levels (around 44 and below but not positive) fluxing a bloodgill from one corner will aggro both. This changes around 45 and you have to individually flux all the bloodgills, or else you will just solo pull them.<br>
<br>
How to flux - Target a bloodgill at the pillar. Start swimming to the other pillar, and use the short sides (don't swim across the long walls, use the front/back pillar of one side). When you get about halfway flux the goblin you have targeted. The halfway point is approximately marked by a dividing line in the roof. Keep swimming and target the next bloodgill as you swim into range. Swim up and over him and head for the water surface beside the top of the pillar. Flux him just before you break surface. You now have 2 aggro'd. Make a half circle back to the first pillar and then dive back down and repeat for the remaining 2 goblins. If you are getting whacked you are doing it wrong. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearedanymore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfeared anymore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/01 11:55:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding Bloodgills..</span><hr size=1> So i take it these are the goblins in the roof area, not the ones near the lake floor ?  By the time I break the surface after having agroed them with flux staff, they have closed the gap, beat through the damage shield, and have done 500 hp damage IF I am lucky and have not been stunned..<br>
<br>
Ill keep trying hehe, what a pain...where else is there comparable EXP that is better suited for quading (IE Dires in Iceclad) for light races ?  Just bloodgills it seems 44+ for light races then ? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nyargle>Nyargle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/01 12:40:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding Bloodgills..</span><hr size=1> Once you learn the tricks to fighting Bloodgills it becomes super easy.  One thing I would advise is making sure you know how long your levitate is going to last, because if it runs out after you start pulling you could run into problems.<br>
<br>
At 49 the exp is almost as fast if you are doing one at a time.  Use ice comet instead of temperate flux, the goblin flees instantly.  Then you can finish him off with a 300 damage nuke.  Between goblins go up for a breath of air and everything's fine.<br>
<br>
I got decent exp for bloodgills all the way until 51. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaultar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maultar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/01 12:57:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quadding Bloodgills..</span><hr size=1> Has anyone tried that zone north of DL when they are nearing 50 or even 49?  What are those drones worth?  I heard they can be good exp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uknolanncaelestis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knolann Caelestis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/01 5:21:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> The goblins out in front on the lake bottom take more skill to pull, but can be done without getting clobbered. I prefer the top corner ones so I don't have to waste time killing a marauder. It is also impolite to kill the marauder if you don't need the medallion.<br>
<br>
Just practice. Make sure your swimming skill is up, mine was maxed or near maxed (194+). Strafe swimming might also help ya but it shouldn't be necessary.<br>
<br>
I prefer to refresh levitate  before every kite. Losing it in mid kite is a fast way to die <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearedanymore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfeared anymore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/01 9:57:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Thanks all, I think I got it...and level 45 last night <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
